Say I have to following controller:
``` c#
[Route("My")]
public class MyController : ControllerBase
{
    [HttpGet]
    public void MyAction([Required] string queryParm)
    {

    }
}
```
And the following code:
``` c#
var apiDescriptionsProvider = app.ApplicationServices.GetRequiredService<IApiDescriptionGroupCollectionProvider>();
var parameterDescription = apiDescriptionsProvider.ApiDescriptionGroups.Items.Single().Items.Single().ParameterDescriptions.Single();
var isBindingRequired = parameterDescription.ModelMetadata.IsBindingRequired;
var isRequired = parameterDescription.ModelMetadata.IsRequired;
```

I'd expect both `isBindingRequired` and `isRequired` to be true. Both are however false.
I also inspected `ModelMetadata.MetadataKind` which had a value of `Type` instead of `Parameter` which I expect is the underlying cause.

Am I doing something wrong, or is this a bug? When I call the API from my browser without supplying `queryParm`, the model state is invalid. So that part is going right.
